==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metamer
<hw>Met"a*mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Metamere</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of several
metameric forms of the same substance, or of different substances having
the same composition; <as>as, xylene has three <ex>metamers</ex>, viz.,
orthoxylene, metaxylene, and paraxylene</as>; an isomer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metamere</ent>⟦br⟧
